{
  "texts": [
    "SH: Among the possible constraints or biases, you forgot to mention mirroring: the relationship between perception and production (as in mirror-neurons and imitation).",
    "Do you think that any such effects are at play in your verbal interactions with your users and with your database?",
    "In language, this mirroring effect is seen in how children learn to speak and understand language by imitating the sounds, words, and sentences they hear from adults and peers.",
    "This process is akin to mirroring in that the LLM reflects the patterns, styles, and structures present in its training data.",
    "However, it's important to note that this is not mirroring in the neurological sense, as LLMs do not have sensory experiences or consciousness."
  ]
}